.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH libertai 1  "libertai 0.4.2" 
.SH NAME
libertai \- LibertAI CLI — inference, images, and agent\-tool launchers.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBlibertai\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
LibertAI CLI — inference, images, and agent\-tool launchers.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
libertai\-login(1)
Log in (browser sign\-in or paste an API key)
.TP
libertai\-logout(1)
Clear saved credentials (secrets removed; other settings kept)
.TP
libertai\-status(1)
Show current auth state and defaults
.TP
libertai\-keys(1)
Manage API keys
.TP
libertai\-models(1)
List available models
.TP
libertai\-ask(1)
One\-shot prompt, non\-streaming
.TP
libertai\-chat(1)
Streaming chat REPL (Ctrl\-D to exit)
.TP
libertai\-search(1)
Web search via LibertAI\*(Aqs search API (search.libertai.io)
.TP
libertai\-fetch(1)
Fetch a URL and return cleaned article text via search.libertai.io
.TP
libertai\-image(1)
Generate an image
.TP
libertai\-run(1)
Launch an arbitrary command with LibertAI env vars injected
.TP
libertai\-claude(1)
Launch Claude Code against LibertAI
.TP
libertai\-opencode(1)
Launch OpenCode against LibertAI
.TP
libertai\-aider(1)
Launch Aider against LibertAI
.TP
libertai\-claw(1)
Launch Claw Code (ultraworkers/claw\-code) against LibertAI
.TP
libertai\-hermes(1)
Launch Hermes Agent against LibertAI
.TP
libertai\-code(1)
LibertAI\*(Aqs own coding agent, powered by pi_agent_rust
.TP
libertai\-agents(1)
One screen for all your coding\-agent sessions
.TP
libertai\-mcp(1)
Run an MCP server exposing LibertAI web search and page fetch over stdio
.TP
libertai\-config(1)
Config file operations
.TP
libertai\-skills(1)
Install/list/uninstall the bundled agent skills (image gen etc)
.TP
libertai\-sandbox(1)
Inspect the bash\-sandbox configuration
.TP
libertai\-import(1)
Import data from other coding agents into a LibertAI session
.TP
libertai\-completions(1)
Print a shell completion script to stdout.
.TP
libertai\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.4.2
